غنّت"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroD","text_ar":"الاَرْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The land had its herbs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, tall, full-grown,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of full height, and in blossom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Agn~ Aln~axolu","text_ar":"اغنّ النَّخْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The palm-trees attained to maturity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gan~a","text_ar":"غَنَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Agn~ Als~iqaA='u","text_ar":"اغنّ السِّقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The skin became filled"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.)       -A2-  And [it is also trans.:] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Agn~ A@ll~`hu guSonahu","text_ar":"اغنّ ا@للّٰهُ غُصْنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made its branch beautiful and bright."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n32495","headword_ar":"اَغَنُّ","root":"gn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who speaks"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a nasal sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twang,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"through"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his nose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who speaks from his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayaA$iym","text_ar":"خَيَاشِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. here meaning (as expl. before) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"innermost parts of the airpassages of the nose"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Msb:) or, accord. to AZ, (Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose speech flows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K, *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passes forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahaAp","text_ar":"لَهَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. (as expl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gun~apN","text_ar":"غُنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pillars, of the soft palate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furthest part of the mouth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh, K, TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gan~aA='u","text_ar":"غَنَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  It is also applied to a gazelle ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaboYN","text_ar":"ظَبْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whose cry issues from his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayaA$iym","text_ar":"خَيَاشِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. above]: J has erred in saying that it is applied to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tayor","text_ar":"طَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. birds, or flying things]: (K:) or if by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tyr","text_ar":"طير"},{"kind":"text","text":"he mean flies ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbN","text_ar":"ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), his saying thus is not a mistake, for it is applied to them [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making a humming sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAdK A^agan~u","text_ar":"وَادٍ اَغَنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A valley abounding with herbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for to such the flies constantly keep, and in their sounds is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gun~ap","text_ar":"غُنَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugin~N","text_ar":"مُغِنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And (for this reason, TA) one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoDapN gan~aA='u","text_ar":"رَوْضَةٌ غَنَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A meadow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abounding with herbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the winds pass with a sound that is not clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a confused, humming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"murmuring, sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of the denseness of its herbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And [for the same reason one says]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$obN A^agan~u","text_ar":"عُشْبٌ اَغَنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Herbs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage, tall, full-grown,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of full height, and in blossom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And (hence also, S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroyapN gan~aA='u","text_ar":"قَرْيَةٌ غَنَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A town,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"village,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abounding with inhabitants"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and buildings"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and herbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that in it is heard the hum of men and women and of flies &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarofN A^agon~u","text_ar":"حَرْفٌ اَغْنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A letter from"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the utterance of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which results what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gun~ap","text_ar":"غُنَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the nasal sound thus termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gun~apN","text_ar":"غُنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","Mgh","TA","K"]}]}}